<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14121">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Law.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13494">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Define law. Tell some of its sources. Describe the functions it serves.
      <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a
        href="https://guides.law.sc.edu/c.php?g=315539&amp;p=10379907"
        target="_blank"
        >Sources of Law (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13477">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Discuss TWO of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13477 mb-requirement-id-13478">
        (a) Justinian's Code, the Code of Hammurabi, and the Magna Carta
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/Code-of-Justinian"
          target="_blank"
          >Code of Justinian (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/AeQV7RcHku0" target="_blank"
          >Code of Justinian (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.history.com/articles/hammurabi" target="_blank"
          >Code of Hammurabi (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/b0STcHOptgM" target="_blank"
          >Code of Hammurabi (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7xo4tUMdAMw" target="_blank"
          >Magna Carta (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13477 mb-requirement-id-13479">
        (b) The development of the jury system <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.history.com/articles/trial-by-jury-origins-founding-fathers"
          target="_blank"
          >Origins of Modern Jury System (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13477 mb-requirement-id-13480">
        (c) Two famous trials in history <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/RK7B-m6ZKyw" target="_blank"
          >Famous Trials That Shaped Legal History (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13496">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Tell what civil law is; tell what criminal law is. Tell the main
      differences between them. Give examples of each. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a
        href="https://www.lawhelp.org/resource/the-differences-between-criminal-court-and-ci"
        target="_blank"
        >Differences Between Criminal Court and Civil Court (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Zg5ex8WZUao" target="_blank"
        >What Is the Difference Between Civil Cases and Criminal Cases?
        (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13497">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Ask five people (not more than one from your immediate family) about the
      role of law enforcement officers in our society. Discuss their answers
      with them. Report your findings to your counselor.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13498">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Discuss with your counselor several laws that were passed to protect the
      consumer and the seller. Describe several organizations that provide help
      to consumers and sellers. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/e5vmBmyZbqY" target="_blank"
        >Consumer Protection Law Explained (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13481">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13481 mb-requirement-id-13482">
        (a) Attend a session of a civil or criminal court. Write 250 words or
        more on what you saw.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13481 mb-requirement-id-13483">
        (b) Plan and conduct a mock trial with your troop or school class or
        other group. After the trial is over, discuss it with the group.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/jzGBkWpAEQ8" target="_blank"
          >Law Merit Badge Mock Trial (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qwS1suoSimc" target="_blank"
          >How Does a Mock Trial Work? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13499">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Arrange a visit with a lawyer who works for a business, bank, title
      company, or government agency. Find out his or her duties and
      responsibilities. Report what you have learned.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13500">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Explain the requirements for becoming a lawyer in your state. Describe how
      judges are selected in your state. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/NvlnLPZaSnk" target="_blank"
        >How To Become a Lawyer (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13501">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Make a list of 15 jobs that deal with some aspects of law or legal
      processes. Tell which you prefer. Why? <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://legalcareerpath.com/" target="_blank"
        >List of Legal Careers (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13495">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10. </span>
      Tell where people can go to obtain the help of a lawyer if they are unable
      to pay for one. Tell what you can do if you can afford a lawyer but do not
      know of any in your area. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://www.lsc.gov/" target="_blank"
        >Legal Help Program If You Cannot Afford an Attorney (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.americanbar.org/groups/public_education/resources/public-information/how-do-i-find-a-lawyer-/"
        target="_blank"
        >How To Find An Attorney (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/8V35XuRqr-c" target="_blank"
        >How Do I Find a Lawyer (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13484">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 11. </span>
      Discuss with your counselor the importance in our society of TWO of the
      following areas of the law or process:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13484 mb-requirement-id-13485">
        (a) Administrative <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://law.pepperdine.edu/blog/posts/understanding-administrative-law.htm"
          target="_blank"
          >Understanding Administrative Law (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qzgtxM4hsCQ" target="_blank"
          >Who Regulates Daily Life? | Administrative Law Explained (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13484 mb-requirement-id-13502">
        (b) Alternative Dispute Resolution <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/alternative_dispute_resolution"
          target="_blank"
          >Alternative Dispute Resolution (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/bUmWRqlL6oM" target="_blank"
          >Alternative Dispute Resolution - An Explanation &amp; Overview
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13484 mb-requirement-id-13486">
        (c) Bankruptcy <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.uscourts.gov/court-programs/bankruptcy/bankruptcy-basics"
          target="_blank"
          >Bankruptcy Basics (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/jobpaNCY-LU" target="_blank"
          >Bankruptcy Basic (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13484 mb-requirement-id-13503">
        (d) Biotechnology <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://testmaxprep.com/blog/bar-exam/biotechnology-law%20"
          target="_blank"
          >What Is Biotechnology Law? (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ytzwXOaIvqQ" target="_blank"
          >Biotech Regulation (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13484 mb-requirement-id-13487">
        (e) Environmental <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/nq3racsBxg0" target="_blank"
          >Environmental Law: A Short Introduction (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13484 mb-requirement-id-13488">
        (f) Family <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.metlife.com/stories/legal/what-is-family-law/"
          target="_blank"
          >Family Law (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7gGHZ6OHIXI" target="_blank"
          >Family Law Explained (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13484 mb-requirement-id-13489">
        (g) Immigration <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.law.georgetown.edu/your-life-career/career-exploration-professional-development/for-jd-students/explore-legal-careers/practice-areas/immigration-law/"
          target="_blank"
          >Immigration Law (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/f790amgB6fo" target="_blank"
          >Immigration Law Explained (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13484 mb-requirement-id-13490">
        (h) Information Technology <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.ebsco.com/research-starters/computer-science/information-technology-law-cyberlaw"
          target="_blank"
          >Information Technology Law (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/asByYA3rSCo" target="_blank"
          >Cyber Law Explained (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13484 mb-requirement-id-13491">
        (i) Intellectual Property, (Copyright, Patents and Trademarks) <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.law.georgetown.edu/your-life-career/career-exploration-professional-development/for-jd-students/explore-legal-careers/practice-areas/intellectual-property-law/"
          target="_blank"
          >Intellectual Property Law (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/JyafmkfQDiY" target="_blank"
          >Intellectual Property Law Explained (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13484 mb-requirement-id-13492">
        (j) International <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/international_law"
          target="_blank"
          >International Law (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/jTzKgI68VLc" target="_blank"
          >What Is International Law (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13484 mb-requirement-id-13493">
        (k) Privacy <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.law.georgetown.edu/your-life-career/career-exploration-professional-development/for-jd-students/explore-legal-careers/practice-areas/tech-and-privacy-law/%20%20%20"
          target="_blank"
          >Tech Law &amp; Privacy Law (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_Wh8iNhNgpc" target="_blank"
          >Understanding the Basics of US Privacy Laws (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
